[49m[38;5;10m+    509[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ### Prerequisites
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    510[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    511[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Requirement | Details |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    512[0m:[38;5;10m[49m |-------------|---------|
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    513[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | AWS Services | Amazon Bedrock (with Claude model access enabled), Bedrock Agents, Bedrock Knowledge Bases, Bedrock Guardrails, Amazon OpenSearch Serverless (vector + lexical), AWS Lambda, AWS Step Functions, Amazon API Gateway, AWS WAF, Amazon DynamoDB, Amazon S3 (with Object Lock), AWS HealthLake, Amazon EventBridge, Amazon Kinesis Data Firehose, AWS Glue, Amazon Athena, Amazon QuickSight, Amazon Pinpoint (SMS), Amazon Connect (voice), Amazon SageMaker (optional), AWS Secrets Manager, AWS KMS (customer-managed keys), AWS CloudTrail, AWS IAM (with attribute-based access control) |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    514[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | IAM Permissions | Per-Lambda least-privilege roles. Attribute-based access control on per-trial scopes. Separate roles for the conversation-runtime Lambda, each action-group Lambda, the Step Functions state machines, the analytics pipeline, and the coordinator-workflow integration. Read-only roles for principal investigators and sponsor recruitment teams (per BAA). Specific actions include `bedrock:InvokeAgent`, `bedrock:Retrieve`, `bedrock-agent:InvokeAgent`, `lambda:InvokeFunction`, `dynamodb:GetItem/PutItem/UpdateItem` scoped to per-trial table prefixes, `s3:PutObject` to the audit bucket with Object Lock policies, `kms:Decrypt/Encrypt` scoped to per-trial KMS keys, `healthlake:ReadResource/SearchResource` scoped to consent-gated patient sets, `events:PutEvents` to the recruitment lifecycle bus, and similar service-specific actions |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    515[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | BAA | AWS BAA in place. BAAs with all third-party integrations: the coordinator-workflow tooling vendor, the trial-data-management-system vendor, the EHR vendor, the sponsor-portal vendor, and any sponsor recruitment vendor. All conversation channels (web, app, SMS, voice) covered |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    516[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Encryption | KMS customer-managed keys with separate keys for the IRB-approved-content corpus (institutional research-content key), the prescreen artifacts (research-data key), the conversation audit log (research-audit key), and the operational state (operational-state key). TLS 1.3 in transit on every endpoint. Per-channel encryption: TLS for web and app, carrier-grade SMS encryption with PHI-minimization in SMS payloads, encrypted voice for Connect with recording retention per institutional research-data-retention policy |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    517[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | VPC | Conversation-runtime Lambda in a VPC with VPC endpoints for Bedrock, Bedrock Agents, Bedrock Knowledge Bases, S3, DynamoDB, KMS, Secrets Manager, EventBridge, and CloudWatch. Private subnets only. NAT for outbound where required by integrations. Strict security groups |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    518[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | CloudTrail | All API activity logged to a dedicated CloudTrail trail in a separate AWS account (the institutional security-and-audit account) with S3 Object Lock retention. CloudTrail Data Events for the prescreen artifact store and the conversation audit store. Per-trial CloudTrail-derived audit views for IRB inspection |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    519[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | IRB Approvals | The IRB approves the recruitment script, the prescreen flow, the FAQ corpus, the disclosures, the eligibility-criteria classification (tier 1 / tier 2 / tier 3), the pause-and-amendment-handling plan, the coordinator-handoff process, the data-collection plan including representativeness data, the patient-information-retention plan, the language scope (English plus other supported languages), and any institutional supplementary recruitment material. Each is version-controlled and effective-date-stamped. <!-- TODO: verify; IRB approval scope for AI-driven recruitment platforms is institution-specific; the listed items are the conventional scope; specific institutional IRBs may require additional scope -->|
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    520[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Sample Data | Synthetic patient data only in development. Use Synthea-derived clinical data and synthetic eligibility-prescreen scenarios. The institutional research-recruitment team typically provides a curated set of de-identified historical recruitment conversations for development and testing, with explicit IRB approval for the development use. Never use real participant PHI in development |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    521[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Cost Estimate | Per-conversation cost: Bedrock model invocation (claude-3-haiku to claude-3-sonnet for the conversation, ~$0.05 to $0.40 per typical 20-turn conversation depending on model and context length), Bedrock Knowledge Bases retrieval (~$0.01 to $0.05 per conversation), OpenSearch Serverless vector queries (variable; for an institution running ~100,000 conversations per quarter, OCU-based pricing typically $200-1500 per month), Lambda invocations ($1-5 per 100,000 invocations at the modest memory profile), DynamoDB reads and writes (single-digit dollars per 100,000 conversations), S3 storage and access (single-digit cents per conversation for typical retention), and Pinpoint or Connect for the channel layer (per-message and per-minute costs). Coordinator-workflow integration costs are typically the dominant operational cost line and are institutional rather than AWS. <!-- TODO: verify; Bedrock and AWS pricing changes regularly; pricing-page references are in the Resources section --> Total per-conversation AWS cost typically $0.20 to $2.00 depending on conversation length, model selection, and channel. Per-handoff cost (which is the meaningful business unit) typically $8 to $25 once the AWS infrastructure cost, the IRB-content authoring amortization, and the coordinator-team capacity allocation are summed. Numbers vary widely with trial complexity and institutional context |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    522[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    523[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ### Ingredients
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    524[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    525[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Service / Component | Role in this Recipe |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    526[0m:[38;5;10m[49m |---------------------|---------------------|
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    527[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Amazon Bedrock (Claude) | Conversation engine. Generates patient-facing responses grounded in retrieved IRB-approved content, emits structured tool calls for eligibility evaluation, prescreen capture, handoff scheduling, and trial-state lookup |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    528[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Bedrock Agents | Multi-step LLM-and-tool orchestration. Action groups bind the Bedrock agent to the recruitment-specific Lambda tools |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    529[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Bedrock Knowledge Bases | Per-trial IRB-approved content corpus. The trial summary, the FAQ entries, the visit-schedule summary, the study-procedure summary. Source content is version-stamped with IRB-approval metadata |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    530[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Bedrock Guardrails | Recruitment-specific safety filtering. Denied topics include medical advice, recommendations on whether to enroll, trial comparisons, and protocol-confidential disclosure |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    531[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Amazon OpenSearch Serverless | Vector and lexical index for the IRB-approved content corpus and the per-trial FAQ corpus. Hybrid retrieval combines vector and BM25 search |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    532[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | AWS Lambda (FAQ Retrieval) | Tool that retrieves and reranks IRB-approved FAQ entries for a patient-question turn |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    533[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | AWS Lambda (Eligibility Evaluation) | Tool that runs deterministic per-criterion logic for tier 1 criteria, captures patient-reported tier 2 data, and flags tier 3 criteria for coordinator review |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    534[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | AWS Lambda (Prescreen Capture) | Tool that persists prescreen artifacts to the prescreen store with patient-reported tags, criterion versions, and timestamps |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    535[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | AWS Lambda (Handoff Scheduling) | Tool that builds the structured handoff packet, posts to the coordinator queue, and confirms with the patient |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    536[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | AWS Lambda (Trial State Lookup) | Tool that reads the current trial state, amendment status, and recruitment-pause status from the trial-state cache |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    537[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | AWS Lambda (Emergency Routing) | Tool that interrupts the recruitment conversation when continuous safety screening detects an acute emergency, routes to the appropriate emergency pathway, and posts an emergency event |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    538[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | AWS Step Functions | Trial-onboarding-and-publishing workflow, IRB-amendment rollout workflow, in-flight-conversation amendment-transition workflow, post-conversation handoff fan-out, and reconciliation jobs against the coordinator-workflow tooling |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    539[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Amazon API Gateway with WAF | Recruitment-platform front door. WAF applies bot defense, rate limiting, and request validation. API Gateway terminates TLS, applies per-channel authentication, and routes to the conversation runtime |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    540[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Amazon DynamoDB | Operational state store. Tables include conversation-state, prescreen-artifacts, handoff-packets, trial-state-cache, per-conversation audit-headers, and per-cohort funnel-counter state |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    541[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Amazon S3 with Object Lock | IRB-grade record store. Holds full conversation transcripts, prescreen-artifact documents, handoff packets at handoff time, coordinator-disposition records, and IRB-approved-content versions in effect during each conversation. Compliance-mode Object Lock enforces retention |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    542[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | AWS HealthLake | Patient longitudinal clinical context for chart-aware eligibility prescreen, where the patient is institutionally known and consent permits. FHIR-native model |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    543[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Amazon EventBridge | Recruitment lifecycle event bus. Conversation-started, disclosure-acknowledged, prescreen-started, prescreen-completed, handoff-initiated, handoff-accepted, coordinator-disposition-recorded, trial-state-changed, amendment-published, recruitment-paused, recruitment-resumed, recruitment-closed |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    544[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Amazon Kinesis Data Firehose | Streams audit and analytics events to S3 with format normalization and partitioning by trial, date, and channel |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    545[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | AWS Glue with Amazon Athena | Per-cohort recruitment-funnel analytics, per-trial recruitment-equity dashboards, and diversity-action-plan reporting queries |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    546[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Amazon QuickSight | Per-cohort recruitment-funnel dashboards, per-trial diversity-action-plan reports, operational-handoff-aging dashboards, equity-monitoring dashboards |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    547[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Amazon Pinpoint | SMS recruitment messaging with TCPA-compliant 10DLC-registered messaging. Entry confirmations, handoff confirmations, and follow-up reminders where the patient has consented to SMS |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    548[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Amazon Connect | Voice channel for the recruitment conversation. Voice-friendly disclosure language, slower pacing, and accessibility-aware design. Crisis-pathway integrity preserved |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    549[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Amazon SageMaker (optional) | Optional home for institution-trained models: custom embedding model fine-tuned for clinical-terminology robustness, eligibility-likelihood prior model for handoff prioritization, representativeness-monitoring model for emerging-cohort-disparity detection |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    550[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | AWS Secrets Manager | Coordinator-workflow tooling credentials, trial-data-management-system credentials, sponsor-portal credentials, EHR research-flag credentials. Standard rotation cadence |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    551[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | AWS KMS | Customer-managed keys per data class: research-content key (IRB-approved corpus), research-data key (prescreen artifacts), research-audit key (conversation audit), operational-state key (operational state). Per-trial key policies where institutional policy requires |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    552[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | AWS CloudTrail | All API activity logged to a dedicated trail in a separate AWS account with Object Lock retention. CloudTrail Data Events for prescreen-artifact store and conversation audit store |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    553[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | AWS IAM (with ABAC) | Identity and access. Per-trial access scopes via attribute-based access control. Per-role least-privilege. Read-only access scopes for sponsor-recruitment teams per BAA |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    554[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
