[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1343[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1344[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The recruitment-funnel-monitoring layer reports per-cohort outcomes:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1345[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1346[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Cohort | Conversations | Disclosure Acked | Prescreen Started | Prescreen Completed | Eligible Pending | Handoff Confirmed | Coordinator Accepted | Consented | Randomized |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1347[0m:[38;5;10m[49m |--------|---------------|------------------|-------------------|---------------------|------------------|-------------------|----------------------|-----------|------------|
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1348[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | All | 1,247 | 1,108 | 982 | 871 | 412 | 367 | 312 | 184 | 156 |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1349[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Spanish-language | 184 | 168 | 152 | 137 | 71 | 65 | 56 | 36 | 32 |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1350[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Rural geography | 263 | 230 | 209 | 188 | 88 | 76 | 62 | 31 | 26 |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1351[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Black or African American | 142 | 124 | 113 | 98 | 47 | 41 | 33 | 22 | 18 |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1352[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1353[0m:[38;5;10m[49m <!-- TODO: replace illustrative numbers with site-specific values from a representative trial deployment once such data is available -->
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1354[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1355[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Where it struggles:**
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1356[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - Trials with extremely complex eligibility (oncology trials with twenty-plus structured criteria including specific imaging-finding requirements, pediatric trials with developmental-stage-specific criteria, rare-disease trials with diagnostic-confirmation requirements that require specialty workup) push the assistant toward "uncertain-pending-coordinator-verification" results far more often than they push toward "clearly-eligible-pending-coordinator-confirmation," which means the coordinator workload reduction is smaller and the architectural value is concentrated in the FAQ and disclosure work rather than the eligibility prescreen
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1357[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - Trials where the IRB has approved only generic disqualification language ("you do not appear to meet the eligibility criteria") produce patient-experience friction because the patient does not learn why; the architecture cannot extemporize beyond what the IRB has approved
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1358[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - Patients with low health literacy, patients with limited English proficiency in unsupported languages, and patients with cognitive impairments may need a coordinator-led prescreen rather than the assistant; the assistant detects these scenarios via patient signals (repeated clarification requests, indications of confusion, surrogate-decision-maker patterns) and routes accordingly
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1359[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - Decentralized-trial recruitment where the patient is geographically distant from any active site requires the assistant to integrate with telehealth-and-home-visit logistics, which adds an architectural layer that not all institutions have built out
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1360[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - Recruitment in trials with high placebo-arm aversion (patients who hear "placebo" and immediately disengage) requires careful IRB-approved placebo-language framing; the assistant cannot soften the placebo framing beyond what the IRB has approved
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1361[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - Multi-trial scenarios where the patient is a candidate for two or more open trials in the same therapeutic area require careful no-comparison framing; the assistant explicitly avoids comparing trials and discusses one at a time
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1362[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - Pediatric and surrogate-decision-maker scenarios add identity-and-consent complexity that the baseline architecture handles but that requires per-trial customization
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1363[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
