[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1596[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Estimated Implementation Time
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1597[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1598[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Tier | Scope | Time |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1599[0m:[38;5;10m[49m |------|-------|------|
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1600[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Basic | Single trial in a single therapeutic area, single language (English), single channel (in-app or web chat), curated IRB-approved-content corpus reviewed by clinical leadership and the institutional IRB, eligibility-criterion tier classification with named clinical-leadership ownership per criterion, basic eligibility-evaluation engine for tier 1 criteria, basic trial-state lifecycle (open, paused, closed), basic coordinator-handoff infrastructure with manual coordinator-team queue routing, basic FDA-strategy artifact reviewed by FDA-experienced regulatory counsel, basic per-cohort funnel monitoring at the institutional-aggregate level, basic audit pipeline with research-grade retention, named institutional research-recruitment platform manager, multi-quarter IRB-content authoring | 9-15 months |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1601[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Production-ready | Multi-trial across one or two therapeutic areas, multi-channel (web, app, SMS with TCPA-compliant 10DLC-registered messaging), multi-language (English plus Spanish at minimum with clinically-validated translations), full IRB-approved-content corpus per trial with annual review cycles, full eligibility-criterion tier classification with held-out-validation calibration of the eligibility-evaluator, full trial-state lifecycle with IRB-amendment-rollout workflows, full coordinator-handoff workflow with coordinator-team workflow integration and SLA-aware routing, full per-cohort funnel monitoring with launch-gate discipline, full diversity-action-plan reporting pipeline for FDA-regulated trials, full FDA-strategy artifact and (where applicable) IND-or-IDE recruitment-material registration, full HIPAA-grade compliance review including state-specific recruitment-consent compliance, full per-cohort equity monitoring with launch-gate criteria, full clinician-referral-pathway integration with EHR-side tooling, full EHR-driven prescreen-invitation pathway, named operational owners across institutional clinical leadership, the institutional research-recruitment team, the IRB liaison, the per-trial coordinator teams, the principal investigators, sponsor recruitment teams (where applicable), compliance, regulatory, IT, and patient experience | 18-30 months |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1602[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | With variations | Pediatric trial recruitment with parental permission and pediatric assent, decentralized-clinical-trial recruitment with home-visit and telehealth logistics integration, rare-disease trial recruitment with diagnostic-confirmation pathway, oncology trial recruitment with treatment-history depth, phase 1 healthy-volunteer trial recruitment, diversity-action-plan-aligned recruitment with cohort-targeted outreach, multi-language deployment beyond English plus Spanish, voice-channel deployment with accessibility considerations, hybrid AI-plus-coordinator-led prescreen for complex trials, sponsor-recruitment-vendor-coexistent deployment, post-disqualification trial-matching offer, consent-process-handoff with consent-conversation continuity, long-running participant-engagement extension, decentralized-trial with at-home device-data integration, structured failure-mode labeling continuous-improvement loop, population-health overlay | 12-24 months beyond production-ready |
